headline: Cisco earnings, Fed, House votes on shutdown bill: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Wednesday, November 12, including corporate earnings results from companies like Cisco Systems (CSCO), FanDuel-parent company Flutter Entertainment (FLUT), and Tencent Music Entertainment (TME); commentary from an array of top Federal Reserve officials; and US House lawmakers are expected to vote on the spending bill tomorrow that could possibly end the government shutdown. Yahoo Finance's Invest conference kicks off at 8:00 A.M. this Thursday, November 13, a day filled with high-profile interviews and panel discussions. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Cisco’s Earnings Are Expected to Rise. Results Could Be a ‘Barometer of Enterprise Demand.’
summary: Cisco Systems  earnings could get a boost if demand for artificial intelligence infrastructure has continued to grow.  Cisco  is scheduled to report fiscal first-quarter earnings after the stock market closes on Wednesday.  Analysts surveyed by FactSet expect the networking company to report adjusted earnings of 98 cents a share on revenue of $14.78 billion.
